<subSubSection id="F06D43AA5ED8A62C6ABB8B93272D7336" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E49A0C84D702BA72608F133DC63CC1F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1A790A87108DEAD74B980FBBEC429E77" pageId="0" pageNumber="169">
The specific name is dedicated to the memory of Yuri Leontovich Stshetkin (1919-1995), a Russian lepidopterist, who lived and collected 
<taxonomicName id="305660D84720C83F758AC58FEC8429CC" authorityName="Chretien" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Galacticidae" genus="Zarcinia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
mainly in Tajikistan. He intensively explored the 
<taxonomicName id="5BF9432C1498832C7C37DFB04B2A6662" authorityName="Chretien" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Galacticidae" genus="Zarcinia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
fauna of the upper Vachsch valley (
<bibRefCitation id="52A84035FB338CC25CB8FEA7BB16E6D8" author="Stshetkin, YL" journalOrPublisher="KMK Scientific Press Ltd., St. Petersburg-Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="169" refId="B43" refString="Stshetkin, YL, 1981. Higher Lepidoptera of the semideserts, adjacent mountains and higher mountains in the Vachsch valley (ecological-zoogeographical analysis). In: MN Narzikulov (Ed.) Entomologiceskoe obozreniye Tajikistana [Entomological revue of Tajikistan], Academy of Sciences of Tajikistan SSR, Dushanbe, 3-81. [216 pp]" title="Higher Lepidoptera of the semideserts, adjacent mountains and higher mountains in the Vachsch valley (ecological-zoogeographical analysis). In: MN Narzikulov (Ed.) Entomologiceskoe obozreniye Tajikistana [Entomological revue of Tajikistan], Academy of Sciences of Tajikistan SSR, Dushanbe, 3 - 81. [216 pp]" year="1981">Stshetkin 1981</bibRefCitation>
), where he collected the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
